# Example environment variables consumed by the vendored Node and
# Python subprocess backends inside the mcp-hub image.
#
# Usage:
#   cp .env.example .env
#   # fill in the values below
#   make run
#
# Never commit your filled .env — it is git-ignored.

# ── Microsoft 365 (softeria MS 365 subprocess) ────────────────────────
# Required when using any of the outlook / outlook-calendar / onedrive
# / sharepoint / ms-teams / ms-excel handles.
# Create an Entra ID multi-tenant app per OAUTH.md §1.
MS365_CLIENT_ID=
MS365_CLIENT_SECRET=

# ── Google Workspace (taylorwilsdon subprocess) ──────────────────────
# Required when using any of the google-drive / gmail / google-calendar
# handles. Create an OAuth client in Google Cloud Console per OAUTH.md §2.
GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=
GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=

# ── Outbound HTTP proxy (optional) ────────────────────────────────────
# Point at your egress proxy (e.g. smokescreen) if you want every
# outbound call from the dispatcher AND from the subprocesses to be
# routed through it. Go's net/http and Python httpx both honor these.
# HTTP_PROXY=http://egress.internal:4750
# HTTPS_PROXY=http://egress.internal:4750
# NO_PROXY=localhost,127.0.0.1

# ── Build-time metadata (Makefile / Dockerfile) ──────────────────────
# Override to stamp a version into /health responses:
#   docker build --build-arg VERSION=2026.04.11-abc1234 -t mcp-hub:mine .
# Leave empty to use the default "dev".
# VERSION=
